Package com.ulflander.mining.processors.extract

Processors that extract and format document into an analyzable model.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
AcronymExtractor Try to find some unknown acronyms in the text.
DocumentCleaner Processor that clean a document, intended to run as first processor.
DocumentSplitter Processor that split a document into chapters, and paragraphs.
DocumentTokenizer Select and applies a Tokenization strategy.
KeywordSelector Select some keywords based on tokens frequency.
LanguageDetector Detects language of a document on the global document, then on each sentences.
POSTagger Processor that detects part of speech in text (Using Stanford POSTagger).
RawArticleCleaner Processor that cleanup article contents fromInternet slang such as "Read comments".
TokenAggregator Aggregates tokens.
TokenCleaner Processor that clean a token.
TokenCorpusConsolidation Consolidate sibbling tokens types based on some corpuses.
TokenCorpusGuesser Compare each token to a list of names and add score for token that looks like a name part.
TokenCounter Processor that amount of token for each sentence/paragraph/chapter/doc.
TokenFrequency Creates a list of tokens based on their frequency, populates document "meta.avg_token_frequency" property.
TokenInferConsolidation This processors infers that if a token is a keyword, and another token next to it has no type, then it could be the same type of token.
TokenRegExpGuesser Processor that attempt to give a type to tokens.
TokenSiblingsConsolidation Run on a Sentence: consolidate token scores based on the fact surrounding tokens have the same type.
TokenWeightConsolidation Consolidate weight of tokens based on in-document frequency (any language).
